import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    sns.lineplot(x='year', y='pop', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the trend of population over time?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    sns.scatterplot(x='fertility', y='life_expect', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the relationship between life expectancy and fertility rate?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='life_expect', hue='country', kde=True, element='step', alpha=0.5, bins=20)
    plt.axvline(x=data['life_expect'].median(), color='red', label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['life_expect'].median()))
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of life expectancy across different countries?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data.dropna(subset=['year'])
    data['year'] = data['year'].dt.year
    data = data.groupby(['year', 'cluster']).mean().reset_index()
    sns.barplot(x='cluster', y='fertility', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the average fertility rate of different clusters?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
